Sobels
Ars Praetorian
Registered: Mar 20, 2013Posts: 462
Posted: Thu May 23, 2013 1:55 pm
Resistivity of hard rubber: 10^13 ohm-metersResistivity of air: More than 10^16 ohm-metersIn short, rubber will do even worse than air at protecting you from extremely high voltages. If something can arc through air it can certainly go through rubber like no one's business.The best form of protection against lightning is to have an alternate path for the current to travel in. This is how a lightning rod works- since it is higher up, the current travels through less air and follows a path of less resistance. Think of it as a parallel circuit- most of the current will travel through the path of least resistance.
Last edited by Sobels on Thu May 23, 2013 1:56 pm
