pan2 wrote:Re. shoes, I don't think the belief is that wearing shoes would make you immune to a lightning strike, but rather that lightning will prefer a path of lower resistance and so wearing shoes may make the path through your body marginally less desirable than another nearby path through inanimate objects.The problem with that theory, is that rubber is a better conductor of electricity than air. Sobels wrote:Resistivity of hard rubber: 10^13 ohm-metersResistivity of air: More than 10^16 ohm-metersSo that inch of rubber in your shoes is a more desirable than the equal volume of air right next to it.
